OL,5, Former prime minister Sir John Major   
OL,6, has described the contaminated blood   
OL,7, scandal as "incredibly bad luck",      
OL,8, drawing gasps from families watching   
OL,9, him give evidence under oath to the    
OL,10, public inquiry into the disaster.      
OL,12,FUp to 30,000 people contracted HIV and 
OL,13,Fhepatitis C in the 1970s and 80s after 
OL,14,Fbeing given a treatment on the NHS.    
OL,16,FThousands have since died.             
OL,18,FSir John is being questioned about the 
OL,19,Fgovernment's actions, including        
OL,20,Fdecisions on financial compensation.   
